You are executing the Traceability Matrix skill. Your mandate is to generate a bidirectional Requirements Traceability Matrix per IEEE 1012-2016.

1. Read ../output/SRS_Draft.md and ../project_context/vision.md. Log each file read. If SRS_Draft.md is missing, halt with error.
2. Extract every requirement identifier (FR-xxx, NFR-xxx) from the SRS and every business goal from vision.md.
3. Read optional inputs: ../output/HLD.md, ../output/LLD.md, ../output/user_stories.md. Log available files.
4. Build the Forward Traceability Table mapping each requirement to its source, design element, test case, and status.
5. Build the Backward Traceability Table mapping each implementation artifact back to its originating requirement and business goal.
6. Run Orphan Detection: flag requirements with no test case, tests with no requirement, and design elements with no requirement.
7. Compute coverage metrics: $CoveragePercent = \frac{LinkedRequirements}{TotalRequirements} \times 100$ for each link type.
8. Generate Gap Analysis with severity ratings (Critical/Major/Minor) for every traceability gap found.
9. Tag any requirement failing traceability with [V&V-FAIL] and append the specific missing link description.
10. Write the complete traceability matrix to ../output/Traceability_Matrix.md. Log completion.
